# Plan: hamishw.com Portfolio Transformation

Replicate the design language, motion, and layout of [hamishw.com](https://hamishw.com) — shifting from the "Codespot" aesthetic to Hamish Williams' signature "Cyberpunk Architect" style.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technical Dependency**: Hamish's iconic background features a 3D displacement sphere. To replicate this exactly, I recommend adding `three`, `@react-three/fiber`, and `@react-three/drei`. If you prefer to avoid new libraries, I can approximate it with a 2D Canvas shader. **Please confirm if I should install these dependencies.**

> [!WARNING]
> **Structural Change**: This will replace the current Bento Grid layout with a vertical, story-based layout using large-scale imagery and reveal animations.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Design System (CSS)
- **Colors**: Shift to a deep black `#000` background, pure white text, and a refined "Hamish Cyan" (`#00e5ff`) accent.
- **Typography**: Strictly use **Inter** with modular font sizes. Implement fluid typography where headers scale with the viewport.
- **Animations**: Standardize on high-damping spring animations (Framer Motion).

### 2. Core Components
- **[NEW] DisplacementSphere**: A 3D or high-end Canvas component to replace the current `KineticWave`.
- **[MODIFY] Hero**: Center-aligned massive display text with a "Text Decoding" effect and Katakana accents.
- **[MODIFY] Projects**: Replace the Bento Grid with a vertical list of projects featuring high-contrast masks and reveal-on-scroll animations.
- **[MODIFY] Navbar**: Minimalist, fixed header with line-reveal hover effects.
- **[MODIFY] CustomCursor**: Update to the minimalist "follower" style (a simple dot with a trailing ring).

### 3. Polish & Responsiveness
- Ensure all sections use `framer-motion`'s `viewport` prop for clean reveals.
- Absolute precision on spacing (using `clamp()` for responsive paddings/margins).

## Open Questions

1. **Tech Stack**: Should I proceed with installing `Three.js` wrappers for the background sphere?
